legacy_interaction_p <- get_interaction_p_value(m_add_r_correct_legacy)
```

Under the stricter reached-negative-r criterion, the clearest pattern was an interaction: PlotWise practice helped most when paired with PlotWise lecture/modeling, but not when added after the control lecture. This suggests that reaching a fully negative correlation may require both interactive practice and prior modeling of how to use the tool conceptually.

## 5.2 Intended correlation change model

**Model formula**

`intended_delta_r ~ lecture_type * practice_type + (1 | participantId)`

This linear mixed model tests how much participants changed correlation in the intended direction, not just whether the direction was correct. Larger values indicate more movement in the intended direction.

