# 8. Working Interpretation

The add-points results are not a simple “PlotWise practice is better” story. The most consistent pattern is that PP performs best on correlation-direction outcomes, while CP is often the weakest. That points to alignment between lecture and practice: participants may need to see the PlotWise way of thinking modeled before the practice tool is useful.

 When reached-negative-r is scored by whether final r actually crosses below zero, the interaction becomes clearer.

Prior knowledge does not explain away the pattern. The coded definition scores are fairly similar across groups, and adding them to the models leaves the condition estimates largely unchanged. The main limitation is still the small number of add-points tasks per participant.



